Floods in KwaZulu-Natal have caused damage worth almost a billion rand. The business sector has also been affected. Small Business Development Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams has launched a relief scheme for small businesses. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Small Business Development Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams has launched a relief scheme for small businesses. Floods in KwaZulu-Natal have caused damage worth almost a billion rand. The business sector has also been affected. READ: KZN flood death toll rises to 443 The minister says they are providing R10 million to informal traders. Death toll from the floods now stands at 443. While, 63 more people are still missing.